<div class="featured"><div class="content"><div class="featured-carousel"><div><div class="content-wrapper poster"><img class="mc-auto show" src="https://posters.shoreline.nz/226-small-custom.jpg" width="150" alt="The Mole Agent Poster"></div><div class="content-wrapper text"><h1 class="featured-title">The Mole Agent</h1><p>		When 83-year-old Sergio is sent as an undercover spy to a retirement home to investigate suspected neglect, he learns a deeper lesson on human connection. Nominated for an Academy Award® for Best Documentary Feature, THE MOLE AGENT is a stylish observational documentary and a hilarious and heart-warming spy movie.						</p><a class="btn light" href="/movies/226/">See More</a></div></div><div><div class="content-wrapper poster"><img class="mc-auto show" src="https://posters.shoreline.nz/231-small-custom.jpg" width="150" alt="Aretha Franklin: Respect Poster"></div><div class="content-wrapper text"><h1 class="featured-title">Aretha Franklin: Respect</h1><p>The life story of legendary R&B singer, Aretha Franklin.														</p><a class="btn light" href="/movies/231/">See More</a></div></div><div><div class="content-wrapper poster"><img class="mc-auto show" src="https://posters.shoreline.nz/227-small-custom.jpg" width="150" alt="The Godmother Poster"></div><div class="content-wrapper text"><h1 class="featured-title">The Godmother</h1><p>How did a once underpaid, overworked French-Arabic translator in charge of phone surveillance for a police narcotics unit, earn the name Mama Weed? After Patience Portefeux, realises she knows the mother of one of the drug dealers she is surveilling, she covers for him and finds herself becoming more and more involved in the world of drug trafficking. With her police resources and new insider knowledge, Patience builds her own crime network and goes on to earn the name, Mama Weed. Based on the novel by Hannel Cayre. 																	</p><a class="btn light" href="/movies/227/">See More</a></div></div><div><div class="content-wrapper poster"><img class="mc-auto show" src="https://posters.shoreline.nz/206-small-custom.jpg" width="150" alt="The Justice of Bunny King Poster"></div><div class="content-wrapper text"><h1 class="featured-title">The Justice of Bunny King</h1><p>A triumph over adversity tale about women fighting their way back from the bottom of society.</p><a class="btn light" href="/movies/206/">See More</a></div></div><div><div class="content-wrapper poster"><img class="mc-auto show" src="https://posters.shoreline.nz/223-small-default.jpg" width="150" alt="Eiffel Poster"></div><div class="content-wrapper text"><h1 class="featured-title">Eiffel</h1><p>The government is asking Eiffel to design something spectacular for the 1889 Paris World Fair, but Eiffel simply wants to design the subway. Suddenly, everything changes when Eiffel crosses paths with a mysterious woman from his past.</p><a class="btn light" href="/movies/223/">See More</a></div></div><div><div class="content-wrapper poster"><img class="mc-auto show" src="https://posters.shoreline.nz/210-small-default.jpg" width="150" alt="The Man in the Hat Poster"></div><div class="content-wrapper text"><h1 class="featured-title">The Man in the Hat</h1><p>The Man in the Hat journeys through France in a Fiat 500 accompanied by a framed photograph of an unknown woman. He is pursued by five angry men in a Citroën Dyane. Why are they chasing him? And how can he shake them off?</p><a class="btn light" href="/movies/210/">See More</a></div></div><div><div class="content-wrapper poster"><img class="mc-auto show" src="https://posters.shoreline.nz/224-small-default.jpg" width="150" alt="Stillwater Poster"></div><div class="content-wrapper text"><h1 class="featured-title">Stillwater</h1><p>A father travels from Oklahoma to France to help his estranged daughter, who is in prison for a murder she claims she didn't commit.</p><a class="btn light" href="/movies/224/">See More</a></div></div><div><div class="content-wrapper poster"><img class="mc-auto show" src="https://posters.shoreline.nz/240-small-default.jpg" width="150" alt="The Lost Leonardo Poster"></div><div class="content-wrapper text"><h1 class="featured-title">The Lost Leonardo</h1><p>The Lost Leonardo is the inside story behind the Salvator Mundi, the most expensive painting ever sold at $450 million. From the moment the painting is bought for $1175 at a shady New Orleans auction house, and the restorer discovers masterful Renaissance brushstrokes under the heavy varnish of its cheap restoration, the Salvator Mundi's fate is determined by an insatiable quest for fame, money and power. As its price soars, so do the questions about its authenticity: is this painting really by Leonardo da Vinci? Unravelling the hidden agendas of the richest men and the most powerful art institutions in the world, The Lost Leonardo reveals how vested interests in the Salvator Mundi are of such tremendous power that truth becomes secondary.</p><a class="btn light" href="/movies/240/">See More</a></div></div><div><div class="content-wrapper poster"><img class="mc-auto show" src="https://posters.shoreline.nz/222-small-default.jpg" width="150" alt="Waiting for Anya Poster"></div><div class="content-wrapper text"><h1 class="featured-title">Waiting for Anya</h1><p>During the harrows of WWII, Jo, a young shepherd along with the help of the widow Horcada, helps to smuggle Jewish children across the border from southern France into Spain.</p><a class="btn light" href="/movies/222/">See More</a></div></div><div><div class="content-wrapper poster"><img class="mc-auto show" src="https://posters.shoreline.nz/239-small-custom.jpg" width="150" alt="Bye Bye Morons Poster"></div><div class="content-wrapper text"><h1 class="featured-title">Bye Bye Morons</h1><p>French Comedy A mother goes on a quest to find her son, who she was forced to abandon almost three decades ago. She enlists the help of a burned-out IT security specialist who is being pursued by the anti-terrorist police. Winner of 6 Cesar Awards including Best Director, Best Film and Best Screenplay

